   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stderr",
     "text": [
      "Unsloth: Already have LoRA adapters! We shall skip this step.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "output_type": "stream",
     "name": "stdout",
     "text": [
      "Trainable params (DPO LoRA): 29,933,568\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Wrap policy with NEW LoRA adapter for DPO updates (don't merge SFT — keep stacked)\n",
    "# Unsloth re-applies LoRA on top of the existing PeftModel.\n",
    "model = FastLanguageModel.get_peft_model(\n",
    "    model,\n",
    "    r=16,\n",
    "    lora_alpha=32,\n",
    "    lora_dropout=0.0,\n",
    "    bias=\"none\",\n",
    "    target_modules=[\n",
    "        \"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\",\n",
    "        \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\",\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    use_gradient_checkpointing=\"unsloth\",\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    use_rslora=False,\n",
    "    loftq_config=None,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Trainable params (DPO LoRA): {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad):,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5ee89adf",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "5ee89adf"
   },
   "source": [
    "> **Why no separate `ref_model=` argument?** Modern TRL (≥ 0.12) auto-detects\n",
    "> PEFT models and uses the *base model without the adapter* as the reference.\n",
    "> That's the same memory layout: 1 base + 2 adapter sets in VRAM. No deepcopy\n",
    "> needed."
   ]
  },
