        "# NB3 — DPO Training (the main event)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Stack:** TRL `DPOTrainer` + `DPOConfig(beta=0.1, lr=5e-7)` from deck §5.2.\n",
        "Maps to deck §3 (DPO derivation), §3.4 (failure modes — read closely!), §5.2 (TRL impl).\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Mục tiêu:** train DPO adapter on top of NB1 SFT-mini. Plot reward curves\n",
        "> (cả `chosen_rewards` và `rejected_rewards`). Save adapter to `adapters/dpo/`.\n",
        ">\n",
        "> Đây là **the** notebook quan trọng nhất của lab — 25/100 pts đến từ đây.\n",
        "> Đặc biệt là: **plot cả 2 curve riêng biệt**, không chỉ reward gap (deck §3.4)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "294f159f",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "294f159f"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 0. Setup"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 47,
      "id": "15f93ec5",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "15f93ec5",
        "outputId": "ef083d1d-cb25-446a-cab9-ad13eb1cef65"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "COMPUTE_TIER:    T4\n",
            "BASE_MODEL:      unsloth/Qwen2.5-3B-bnb-4bit\n",
            "DPO hyperparams: beta=0.1  lr=5e-07  epochs=1\n",
            "max_length:      512  (prompt=256)\n",
            "effective batch: 8\n",
            "SFT input:       /content/lab22/adapters/sft-mini\n",
            "output:          /content/lab22/adapters/dpo\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "\n",
        "COMPUTE_TIER = os.environ.get(\"COMPUTE_TIER\", \"T4\").upper()\n",
        "\n",
        "if COMPUTE_TIER == \"T4\":\n",
        "    BASE_MODEL = \"unsloth/Qwen2.5-3B-bnb-4bit\"\n",
        "    MAX_LEN = 512\n",
        "    MAX_PROMPT_LEN = 256\n",
        "    PER_DEVICE_BATCH = 1\n",
        "    GRAD_ACCUM = 8\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    BASE_MODEL = \"unsloth/Qwen2.5-7B-bnb-4bit\"\n",
        "    MAX_LEN = 1024\n",
        "    MAX_PROMPT_LEN = 512\n",
        "    PER_DEVICE_BATCH = 1\n",
        "    GRAD_ACCUM = 4\n",
        "\n",
        "# Hyperparameters from deck §5.2 lines 849–886\n",
        "BETA = float(os.environ.get(\"DPO_BETA\", \"0.1\"))\n",
        "LR = float(os.environ.get(\"DPO_LR\", \"5e-7\"))\n",
        "EPOCHS = int(os.environ.get(\"DPO_EPOCHS\", \"1\"))\n",
        "\n",
        "REPO_ROOT = Path.cwd().parent if Path.cwd().name == \"notebooks\" else Path.cwd()\n",
        "SFT_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"adapters\" / \"sft-mini\"\n",
        "DPO_OUT = REPO_ROOT / \"adapters\" / \"dpo\"\n",
        "PREF_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"data\" / \"pref\" / \"train.parquet\"\n",
        "\n",
        "DPO_OUT.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "assert SFT_PATH.exists(), f\"NB1 must run first — {SFT_PATH} missing\"\n",
        "assert PREF_PATH.exists(), f\"NB2 must run first — {PREF_PATH} missing\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"COMPUTE_TIER:    {COMPUTE_TIER}\")\n",
        "print(f\"BASE_MODEL:      {BASE_MODEL}\")\n",
        "print(f\"DPO hyperparams: beta={BETA}  lr={LR}  epochs={EPOCHS}\")\n",
        "print(f\"max_length:      {MAX_LEN}  (prompt={MAX_PROMPT_LEN})\")\n",
        "print(f\"effective batch: {PER_DEVICE_BATCH * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\n",
        "print(f\"SFT input:       {SFT_PATH}\")\n",
        "print(f\"output:          {DPO_OUT}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 48,
      "id": "affdd8e5",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "affdd8e5"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "assert torch.cuda.is_available(), \"DPO needs a CUDA GPU. See HARDWARE-GUIDE.md.\""
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "c58d7ee8",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c58d7ee8"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Load policy + reference (the VRAM-doubling part)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Critical:** DPO needs the policy (trainable) AND a frozen reference (no grad).\n",
        "The reference is the SFT model at step 0; we load it twice. Unsloth's 4-bit base\n",
        "is shared across copies — only the LoRA adapter differs."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 49,
      "id": "9788b1a9",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 208,
          "referenced_widgets": [
            "6bf433dea57e4575a35920ea328f0846",
            "3479f4b70fac453fa1a92a3596f086d7",
            "517892cc5d39452486a78f6d17275b21",
            "b8c55073f9f14846a6e84aea581b282c",
            "e0fd1c8c40f84dd4a9abdc2f3f2865bb",
            "2484c67184514696ba83c4be5a5edc26",
            "1ea415aaef9542f7b035ac7fb4c7765a",
            "82ff0f59d2f7482881c07616b90f60ba",
            "34fa388ffe324dab8798b7733c8e3e32",
            "9c3a7ff0156b486cb0b018c2a52238e7",
            "dbbfcce69b5643f0859412be4c8c9925"
          ]
        },
        "id": "9788b1a9",
        "outputId": "c9b87576-c3c0-4fbc-b16b-ba66c840f023"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "==((====))==  Unsloth 2026.5.2: Fast Qwen2 patching. Transformers: 5.5.0.\n",
            "   \\\\   /|    Tesla T4. Num GPUs = 1. Max memory: 14.563 GB. Platform: Linux.\n",
            "O^O/ \\_/ \\    Torch: 2.10.0+cu128. CUDA: 7.5. CUDA Toolkit: 12.8. Triton: 3.6.0\n",
            "\\        /    Bfloat16 = FALSE. FA [Xformers = 0.0.35. FA2 = False]\n",
            " \"-____-\"     Free license: http://github.com/unslothai/unsloth\n",
            "Unsloth: Fast downloading is enabled - ignore downloading bars which are red colored!\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/434 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
            ],
            "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
              "version_major": 2,
              "version_minor": 0,
              "model_id": "6bf433dea57e4575a35920ea328f0846"
            }
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "unsloth/Qwen2.5-3B-bnb-4bit does not have a padding token! Will use pad_token = <|PAD_TOKEN|>.\n",
            "Policy: PeftModelForCausalLM with SFT adapter loaded\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel\n",
        "from peft import PeftModel\n",
        "\n",
        "# Policy — gets new DPO LoRA adapter on top of SFT LoRA\n",
        "model, tokenizer = FastLanguageModel.from_pretrained(\n",
        "    model_name=BASE_MODEL,\n",
        "    max_seq_length=MAX_LEN,\n",
        "    dtype=None,\n",
        "    load_in_4bit=True,\n",
        ")\n",
        "if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n",
        "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load SFT adapter on top of base\n",
        "model = PeftModel.from_pretrained(model, str(SFT_PATH), is_trainable=True)\n",
        "print(f\"Policy: {model.__class__.__name__} with SFT adapter loaded\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 50,
      "id": "3a8bc06f",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "3a8bc06f",
        "outputId": "73e48e2d-914d-479b-9816-b822875afeef"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "Unsloth: Already have LoRA adapters! We shall skip this step.\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Trainable params (DPO LoRA): 29,933,568\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Wrap policy with NEW LoRA adapter for DPO updates (don't merge SFT — keep stacked)\n",
        "# Unsloth re-applies LoRA on top of the existing PeftModel.\n",
        "model = FastLanguageModel.get_peft_model(\n",
        "    model,\n",
        "    r=16,\n",
        "    lora_alpha=32,\n",
        "    lora_dropout=0.0,\n",
        "    bias=\"none\",\n",
        "    target_modules=[\n",
        "        \"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\",\n",
        "        \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\",\n",
        "    ],\n",
        "    use_gradient_checkpointing=\"unsloth\",\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    use_rslora=False,\n",
        "    loftq_config=None,\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(f\"Trainable params (DPO LoRA): {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad):,}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "5ee89adf",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5ee89adf"
      },
      "source": [
        "> **Why no separate `ref_model=` argument?** Modern TRL (≥ 0.12) auto-detects\n",
        "> PEFT models and uses the *base model without the adapter* as the reference.\n",
        "> That's the same memory layout: 1 base + 2 adapter sets in VRAM. No deepcopy\n",
        "> needed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "887dfc04",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "887dfc04"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Build DPOConfig (deck §5.2 hyperparameters)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 51,
      "id": "ee18188d",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ee18188d",
        "outputId": "d7f2ffa7-93ae-42a8-f89f-3061f7806def"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "warmup_ratio is deprecated and will be removed in v5.2. Use `warmup_steps` instead.\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "DPOConfig: beta=0.1  lr=5e-07  loss_type=sigmoid\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from trl import DPOConfig\n",
        "\n",
        "dpo_config = DPOConfig(\n",
        "    output_dir=str(DPO_OUT.parent / \"dpo-checkpoints\"),\n",
        "    per_device_train_batch_size=PER_DEVICE_BATCH,\n",
        "    gradient_accumulation_steps=GRAD_ACCUM,\n",
        "    num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,\n",
        "    learning_rate=LR,\n",
        "    beta=BETA,\n",
        "    max_length=MAX_LEN,\n",
        "    max_prompt_length=MAX_PROMPT_LEN,\n",
        "    warmup_ratio=0.1,\n",
        "    lr_scheduler_type=\"cosine\",\n",
        "    logging_steps=10,\n",
        "    save_strategy=\"no\",\n",
        "    optim=\"adamw_8bit\",\n",
        "    bf16=torch.cuda.is_bf16_supported(),\n",
        "    fp16=not torch.cuda.is_bf16_supported(),\n",
        "    seed=42,\n",
        "    loss_type=\"sigmoid\",         # DPO standard (alternatives: ipo, hinge, kto)\n",
        "    report_to=\"none\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"DPOConfig: beta={dpo_config.beta}  lr={dpo_config.learning_rate}  loss_type={dpo_config.loss_type}\")"
      ]
    },
