      },
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "# ⏵ Stage from `notebooks/05_merge_deploy_gguf.py`\n",
        "---"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "254733bc",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "254733bc"
      },
      "source": [
        "# NB5 — Merge + Deploy + GGUF\n",
        "\n",
        "**Stack:** Unsloth `merge_and_unload` + `save_pretrained_gguf(quantization='Q4_K_M')`\n",
        "+ llama-cpp-python smoke test.\n",
        "Maps to deck §7.1 lab brief: \"merge adapter, quantize GGUF, serve với vLLM\".\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Mục tiêu:** export the SFT+DPO adapter as a deployable GGUF Q4_K_M file\n",
        "> (~1.5 GB on 3B / ~4 GB on 7B), then smoke-test it through llama-cpp-python.\n",
        "> Final cell shows the optional vLLM serving command (BigGPU only)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "040f5373",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "040f5373"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 0. Setup"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "3b8a150d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3b8a150d"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import json\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "\n",
        "COMPUTE_TIER = os.environ.get(\"COMPUTE_TIER\", \"T4\").upper()\n",
        "BASE_MODEL = (\n",
        "    \"unsloth/Qwen2.5-3B-bnb-4bit\" if COMPUTE_TIER == \"T4\"\n",
        "    else \"unsloth/Qwen2.5-7B-bnb-4bit\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "MAX_LEN = 512 if COMPUTE_TIER == \"T4\" else 1024\n",
        "\n",
        "REPO_ROOT = Path.cwd().parent if Path.cwd().name == \"notebooks\" else Path.cwd()\n",
        "DPO_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"adapters\" / \"dpo\"\n",
        "MERGED_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"adapters\" / \"merged-fp16\"\n",
        "GGUF_DIR = REPO_ROOT / \"gguf\"\n",
        "MERGED_PATH.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "GGUF_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "assert DPO_PATH.exists(), \"NB3 must run first\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"COMPUTE_TIER:    {COMPUTE_TIER}\")\n",
        "print(f\"DPO adapter:     {DPO_PATH}\")\n",
        "print(f\"merged output:   {MERGED_PATH}\")\n",
        "print(f\"GGUF output:     {GGUF_DIR}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "623c449a",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "623c449a"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "assert torch.cuda.is_available()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "3833597a",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3833597a"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Load DPO model + merge adapter"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "ef8a091d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ef8a091d"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel\n",
        "from peft import PeftModel\n",
        "\n",
        "model, tokenizer = FastLanguageModel.from_pretrained(\n",
        "    model_name=BASE_MODEL,\n",
        "    max_seq_length=MAX_LEN,\n",
        "    dtype=None,\n",
        "    load_in_4bit=True,\n",
        ")\n",
        "if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n",
        "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
        "\n",
        "# Stack SFT-mini → DPO adapters\n",
        "SFT_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"adapters\" / \"sft-mini\"\n",
        "model = PeftModel.from_pretrained(model, str(SFT_PATH))\n",
        "print(f\"Loaded SFT-mini adapter from {SFT_PATH}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "264dcfc2",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "264dcfc2"
      },
      "source": [
        "> **Note:** The DPO adapter trained in NB3 stacks on top of SFT. To get a fully\n",
        "> aligned merged model, we apply both adapters before merging. Unsloth's\n",
        "> `save_pretrained_merged` handles the SFT + DPO + base merge in one shot."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "73db6320",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "73db6320"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Save merged FP16 weights\n",
        "\n",
        "`save_pretrained_merged(method=\"merged_16bit\")` produces a HuggingFace-format\n",
        "directory you can either upload to HF Hub directly OR feed into the GGUF\n",
        "converter in step 3."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "74f6d6eb",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "74f6d6eb"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# This re-loads the model with both SFT and DPO adapters merged into base weights.\n",
        "# Output is FP16 (or BF16 on Ampere+) HF-format weights ready for inference.\n",
        "model.save_pretrained_merged(\n",
        "    str(MERGED_PATH),\n",
        "    tokenizer,\n",
        "    save_method=\"merged_16bit\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(f\"Saved merged FP16 to {MERGED_PATH}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Free GPU memory before GGUF conversion (which spawns a subprocess that needs RAM)\n",
        "import gc\n",
        "\n",
        "del model\n",
        "gc.collect()\n",
        "torch.cuda.empty_cache()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "646907bd",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "646907bd"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Quantize to GGUF Q4_K_M\n",
        "\n",
        "Q4_K_M is the sweet spot: ~4× compression vs FP16, minimal quality loss.\n",
        "Unsloth wraps llama.cpp's `quantize` binary — first run downloads + compiles\n",
        "llama.cpp (~3 min) then quantizes (~30 s)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "92edf035",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "92edf035"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Reload the merged model — Unsloth's GGUF saver expects a live model handle.\n",
        "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel as FLM\n",
        "\n",
        "model, tokenizer = FLM.from_pretrained(\n",
        "    model_name=str(MERGED_PATH),\n",
        "    max_seq_length=MAX_LEN,\n",
        "    dtype=None,\n",
        "    load_in_4bit=False,    # already merged; load full precision\n",
        ")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "564e2db2",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "564e2db2"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Save GGUF in 1 quantization tier (Q4_K_M). Add more tiers below if you want the\n",
        "# +3 \"GGUF release published\" rigor add-on.\n",
        "model.save_pretrained_gguf(\n",
        "    str(GGUF_DIR),\n",
        "    tokenizer,\n",
        "    quantization_method=\"q4_k_m\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(f\"Saved GGUF Q4_K_M to {GGUF_DIR}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "f37d19ed",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f37d19ed"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 3a. Optional — additional quantization tiers (for the +3 rigor add-on)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "15176ac4",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "15176ac4"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Uncomment if you want Q5_K_M + Q8_0 too (~2× total disk space).\n",
        "# Each adds ~30s for an extra GGUF file.\n",
        "#\n",
        "# model.save_pretrained_gguf(str(GGUF_DIR), tokenizer, quantization_method=\"q5_k_m\")\n",
        "# model.save_pretrained_gguf(str(GGUF_DIR), tokenizer, quantization_method=\"q8_0\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "81694b0a",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "81694b0a"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"GGUF files:\")\n",
        "for p in sorted(GGUF_DIR.iterdir()):\n",
        "    if p.suffix == \".gguf\":\n",
        "        size_mb = p.stat().st_size / 1e6\n",
        "        print(f\"  {p.name:50s}  {size_mb:>8.1f} MB\")\n",
        "\n",
        "del model\n",
        "gc.collect()\n",
        "torch.cuda.empty_cache()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "ae8a451d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ae8a451d"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 4. Smoke test with llama-cpp-python"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "22053504",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "22053504"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from llama_cpp import Llama\n",
        "\n",
        "# Find the Q4_K_M GGUF\n",
        "gguf_files = list(GGUF_DIR.glob(\"*Q4_K_M*.gguf\")) + list(GGUF_DIR.glob(\"*q4_k_m*.gguf\"))\n",
        "assert gguf_files, \"No Q4_K_M GGUF found — step 3 may have failed\"\n",
        "gguf_path = gguf_files[0]\n",
        "print(f\"Loading: {gguf_path.name}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# n_gpu_layers=-1 offloads all layers to GPU if compiled with CUDA/Metal/Vulkan\n",
        "llm = Llama(\n",
        "    model_path=str(gguf_path),\n",
        "    n_ctx=MAX_LEN,\n",
        "    n_gpu_layers=-1,           # all layers on GPU; falls back to CPU if no GPU compile\n",
        "    verbose=False,\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(\"Loaded.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8a4de1c9",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8a4de1c9"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 4a. Smoke prompt + response (deliverable: `06-gguf-smoke.png`)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "5c31bdab",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5c31bdab"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "SMOKE_PROMPT = \"Giải thích ngắn gọn (3 câu) cách thuật toán Bubble sort hoạt động.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "response = llm.create_chat_completion(\n",
        "    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": SMOKE_PROMPT}],\n",
        "    max_tokens=200,\n",
        "    temperature=0.0,\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"PROMPT:\\n  {SMOKE_PROMPT}\\n\")\n",
        "print(f\"RESPONSE (Q4_K_M GGUF, llama-cpp-python):\\n  {response['choices'][0]['message']['content']}\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTokens used: {response['usage']}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "031e453e",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "031e453e"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. Optional — vLLM serving (BigGPU only)\n",
        "\n",
        "vLLM provides production-grade OpenAI-compatible serving. **Requires CUDA GPU\n",
        "with ≥ 16 GB VRAM** and `vllm` installed (see `requirements-biggpu.txt`).\n",
        "On T4 tier this cell will OOM. Skip on T4.\n",
        "\n",
        "Run in a SEPARATE terminal (NOT in the notebook — vLLM blocks until killed):\n",
        "\n",
        "```bash\n",
        "pip install vllm                         # once\n",
        "vllm serve adapters/merged-fp16 \\\n",
        "  --port 8000 \\\n",
        "  --max-model-len 1024 \\\n",
        "  --gpu-memory-utilization 0.9\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Then test:\n",
        "\n",
        "```bash\n",
        "curl http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions \\\n",
        "  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n",
        "  -d '{\"model\": \"merged-fp16\", \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}]}'\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why not in the notebook?** vLLM's process model doesn't play nicely with\n",
        "Jupyter — it expects to own the GPU + a long-running HTTP server. Run it as\n",
        "a sidecar process. The deck mentions vLLM as the deploy target; for actual\n",
        "production you'd containerize this command. For the lab, llama-cpp-python in\n",
        "step 4 is the graded artifact."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "5f6d5704",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5f6d5704"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 6. Save deployment metadata"
